The beginning of something great. That was my initial reaction to what I was getting into after purchasing this app. I was pleased with all the filters and fine tuning capabilities provided in the app and I just kept on diving deeper and deeper into everything I understood could be done with an eager mind. Eventually I started blending my edits with the originals to create something entirely new. Then came the realization that shadows could be harnessed to create new textures and depth needed to go deeper into the free world of design. I was turning beautiful woman into dragons and the family dog into the dreaded werewolf in no time. Things just kept getting more and more wonderful the more I kept using this program. And then came the X/Y axis edit feature! The holy grail  of photo editing updates! I don't even use any of the standard photo editing features in this program, I just do everything in the X/Y graph tool. This tool allows you to edit "any" part of the picture in a extremely precise manor. You can edit each of the three colors that make up the color grid in a mathematical manor or choose to use the grid to edit all three colors (red,green,blue) in a logical completely mind blowing method that must be experienced and embraced. I like to take a complex edit and turn it black and white, and just add a touch of scattered color with the rainbow feature and use the X/Y edit tool to completely color in a detailed picture in one step. I mean literally fill in a characters face,hair, scars, clothes, tools, exc in "one" freaking step (4 HOURS LATER)! It's truly an unbelievable experience! I am a true professional who started making real money on my canvas prints (400 bucks for my first) three years ago because of this program, and now I'm getting ready to print out a multi piece edit that's going to be a whopping 8 feet! I love this app with all my heart. Get it, love it, LIVE IT! PIC SAY FREAKING PRO!!!!

Using the "pop colours" effect, Picsay crashes frequently on my Samsung P605 (Note 10.1 '14 Ed. with 3GB RAM, 32GB int. SD and 64 ext. SD, it's certainly not any limitation of the tablet); I've only worked with maximum picture size. This is rather frustrating since there is no autosave of the work I've done before the crash. Conclusion: add an autosave option. This will prevent loss of work due to crash. Plus with a save function (not just export) we could interrupt and continue work on a picture any time; only having the export function, we have to start work on a picture from beginning if we close the app (e. g. I finalise a picture and close the app but find a small mistake I want to correct right afterwards, I can't just correct the mistake in the picture, I have to start over).  Besides that, using my Samsung C-Pen (not the tablet's S-Pen) with rubber pen point to apply the "pop colours" effect frequently triggers the zoom actually assigned to the respective two-finger gesture. It would be cool if I could lock the zoom while doing fine work on an enlarged picture.   Once you've added these functions you'll get five stars (the crash issue is secondary if you add autosave).

Features that I'd like to see in future releases are: (1) Full resolution pictures (although the high res option offered is still pretty good).
